  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6763.84 sitting directly in the massive negative gamma zone (6750-6765 strikes showing -66M to -39M GEX), dealers are aggressively buying this rally and will accelerate purchases on any further upside momentum. The breakout regime combined with the gex_surge event confirms dealers are caught short gamma and forced into momentum-following hedging, creating a feedback loop that should drive price toward the major resistance at 6800 where +36.7M positive gamma awaits. Key inflection points are 6750 (max negative gamma support) and 6800 (max positive gamma resistance) - a break above 6800 could trigger explosive upside as dealers flip from buying to selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong upward momentum with dealers buying every dip until 6800 resistance.",
